      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: resolve QMD Windows shims and guard image URL downloads",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes the Windows QMD shim path and narrows the image URL work into a guarded provider-download path.\n\n- Resolve Windows `.cmd` shims that point at quoted absolute JavaScript entrypoints.\n- Use the real QMD package name, `@tobilu/qmd`, for package-bin fallback resolution.\n- Parse OpenAI-compatible image responses that return `data[].url` instead of `data[].b64_json`.\n- Route provider-returned image URLs through guarded HTTP with bounded reads, MIME validation, scoped same-origin transport reuse, configured media limits, and operation-deadline timeouts.\n- Dropped the unrelated `node-llama-cpp` dependency/lockfile churn from the original PR scope.\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nWindows QMD availability checks no longer fail when `qmd.cmd` wraps a quoted absolute Node entrypoint instead of a `%~dp0`-relative entrypoint. OpenAI-compatible URL-backed image generation responses now produce image assets without using raw fetch or broad private-network carryover.\n\n## Real environment tested\n\n- AWS Crabbox native Windows: `cbx_36917d25d801`, run `run_0dd48bf72083`, hydrate workflow `26722175678`.\n- AWS Crabbox Windows WSL2: `cbx_92cdb109d982`, run `run_740f8e92e641`, hydrate workflow `26721781232`.\n- AWS Crabbox Linux changed gate after rebase: `cbx_0b074a7498e9`, run `run_72f46782c53c`.\n\n## Exact steps or command run after this patch\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/windows-spawn.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/qmd-process.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts src/image-generation/image-assets.test.ts src/image-generation/openai-compatible-image-provider.test.ts extensions/openai/image-generation-provider.test.ts\nnode --max-old-space-size=8192 --import tsx scripts/generate-plugin-sdk-api-baseline.ts --check\nnode scripts/docs-list.js\nnode scripts/check-plugin-sdk-subpath-exports.mjs\ngit diff --check\nnode scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --target linux --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"\n```\n\nNative Windows and WSL2 ran the same focused Vitest set on hydrated Crabbox workspaces. The final Linux changed gate was run after rebasing onto current `origin/main`.\n\n## Evidence after fix\n\n- Local post-rebase focused tests: 6 shards passed, 218 tests total.\n- Native Windows Crabbox focused tests: 6 shards passed, 213 tests total on `run_0dd48bf72083`.\n- WSL2 Crabbox focused tests: 6 shards passed, 215 tests total on `run_740f8e92e641`.\n- Plugin SDK API baseline check passed after regenerating the baseline across the final rebase.\n- SDK subpath export check passed.\n- Autoreview passed clean after the URL-download security/timeout/boundary fixes.\n\n## Observed result after fix\n\n- Quoted absolute Windows `.cmd` QMD shims resolve to direct Node execution without shell fallback.\n- Scoped QMD package fallback resolves through `@tobilu/qmd`.\n- URL-backed OpenAI-compatible image responses are accepted and converted into generated image assets.\n- Cross-origin provider-returned URLs do not inherit provider private-network/dispatcher/auth policy.\n- Same-origin provider-returned URLs keep provider auth/transport policy and still use guarded fetch.\n- URL downloads honor configured generated-media byte limits and share the image operation deadline instead of resetting timeout per download.\n\n## What was not tested\n\nFull live QMD memory indexing/search was not run. The final `pnpm check:changed` gate is blocked by a current `origin/main` type error in untouched `src/channels/message/ingress-queue.test.ts` from `b0679d1f13d`; this PR does not touch channel ingress queue files.\n",
